 Onuminya Innocent in Sokoto After six commissioners and chief of staff in Sokoto State failed to sail through the primary elections of People Democratic Party (PDP) in the state, the state Governor, Aminu Waziri Tambuwal, has sent their names to the state House of Assembly for reinstatement. The six ex-commissioners are Aminu Bala Bodinga, Col Garba Moyi (rtd), Bashir Gidado, Salihu Maidaji, Abdullahi Maigwandu, and Abubakar Maikurdi Ahmad. In a statement issued by the Special Adviser on Media and Publicity to the Governor, Muhammad Bello, he said the governor sent other nominees as follows: Bashir Mohammed Lambara, Abubakar Dange and Abdullahi Yusuf Hausawa to the state House of Assembly for clearance to be appointed as members of the State Executive Council. The statement said the governor has also reinstated his former Chief of Staff, Alhaji Mukhtar Magori. All the seven above voluntarily disengaged from their positions in April 27 to seek elective political offices in line with the provisions of Section 84 (12) of the new Electoral Act which mandates all political appointees seeking elective office to resign ahead of any party primary they plan to participate in.